I first off want to say that all of you screaming "racism" should take a look at the wording of your post. When you address anyone white it is almost always followed with a derrogatory remark. We all have things we do not like about the people and society we live in but one good turn does NOT deserve another.<br>
Where to start ...  /rant on<br>
I value a lot of points here about how language can be a deciding factor on the lives of people within our country. It really has more to do with language than most of you would like to admit. Your own racial bias and background are the basis of an opinion and not always facts.(as mine do here)<br>
To start, I am white. This wasn't a choice I made in the circle of life but like everyone else I live with it. I speak english as my only launguage and have taught my children the same. My parents did not know any other language but English so of course we were taught that as well. My point is that English has always been considered the launguage of this country (no history crap required here), it goes back many generations as with any culture. How is it that now I will have to learn Spanish to accomodate people coming to this country to live, some even illegally ? My children sit in a classroom where spanish is now required and even some teachers are requiring translators. With children living with English as their primary language it is no wonder our education system lacks. With the little money teachers make, asking them to be bilangual as well will certainly weed out the weak ones (sarcasm). I am more concerned that my children learn how to read, write and speak english before trying to decifer a totally different language. (here goes the "children learn quicker than adults .. blah blah.) English is a language used in more countries throughout the world than any other. I expect that my children will be able to communicate well no matter where they choose to be.<br>
I work in a business where there are many different cultures represented yet they all get the concept that we need ONE common language to communicate with. Why is it so difficult for others that come to this country to grasp the same concept. I am not being mean or trying to hurt your feelings when I tell you I don't understand what you are saying, because frankly I just don't understand !<br>
I am totally for diversity and culture entwined within our neighborhoods but at what price ?  I wouldn't go to another country and expect them to change everything surrounding their language to accomodate me .. it's just plain silly.<br>
As for the one that said take some classes and learn other languages ... are you going to pay for it ? Will you come to work for me while I take these classes?  I am raising 4 kids, working full time and trying to live .. how about you ?<br>
